                    <msContents>
                        <summary><p>A Dāwit (Ethiopic Psalter) comprised of Mazmur za-Dāwit (Psalms), Maḥāleya nabiyāt (Canticles), Maḥāleya maḥāley (Song of Songs), Weddāsē Māryām
                                (Praises of Mary), and Anqaṣa berhān (Gate of Light).</p></summary>
                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <title>Dāwit. Psalter</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="gez">Ge'ez</textLang>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                                <locus from="4r" to="152v">4r-152v</locus>
                                <title>Mazmur za-Dāwit. Psalms</title>
                                <note>The ancient titles of the chapters are not preserved except at Pss. 128 and 129 (መኅሌት ፡ ዘመዓርጊሁ ፡). Psalms. 1, 20, and 54 have a new heading (ትንቢት ፡ በእንተ ፡ ክርስቶስ
                                    ፡); all the others are simply designated as መዝሙር ፡ ዘዳዊት ፡.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
