                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="Codex">
                            <supportDesc delim="parchment">
                                <support>
                                    <material key="parchment">Parchment</material> book block.</support>
                                <extent>191 folios: <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                                        <height>200</height>
                                        <width>185</width>
                                    </dimensions>
                                    <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                                        <height>201</height>
                                        <width>190</width>
                                        <depth>80</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>
                                    <p>Modern pencil foliation in Arabic numerals on the top right corner of each recto folio.</p>
                                    <p>Folio 161 has been duplicated twice.</p>
                                </foliation>
                                <collation><p>Twenty-four sections, the first and last sections are made up of 2 bifolios, with the inner-facing outer leaf cut to a stub, perhaps acting as an
                                        endpaper/protection for the rest of the book block. The other sections are made up of 4 bifolios each.</p></collation>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout columns="1 2" writtenLines="15 20">
                                    <p>Folios <locus from="4r" to="172r">4r-172r</locus>: Single columns, 15 to 20 lines per leaf.</p>
                                    <p>Folios <locus from="172v" to="187v">172v-187v</locus>: Double columns, 15 to 20 lines per leaf.</p>
                                    <p>Folios have been pricked and scored to assist in writing.</p>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc test-plan="1">
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic" test-plan-version="ink">
                                <p>Written in a <term ana="#">Ge'ez</term> script, in black and red ink, by a single hand.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p><label>Marginalia</label>: The manuscript contains many erasures and corrections by a second hand.</p>
                            <p>Scribbles on <locus from="1r" to="1r">1r</locus> and <locus from="191r" to="191r">191r</locus>.</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus>, five lines with the beginning of a short calendar for the commemoration of saints.</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="2r" to="2r">2r</locus>, a genealogy in Amharic: ኈልቈ ፡ ዘመድ ። ዋግ ፡ ሹም ፡ ዘረ ፡ ከል ፡ ቢወልድ ፡ ጅር ፡ ባሕራን ። ጅር ፡ ባሕራ ፡ ብትወልድ ፡ አምባ ፡ አፍርስን ። አምባ ፡ ብትወልድ ፡ ዕፍረትን
                                ።</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="2v" to="2v">2v</locus>, two short fragments from the Me'raf (wedding celebration) with musical notation.</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="2v" to="3v">2v-3v</locus>, a short calendar for the commemoration of saints: ሠረቀ ፡ መስከረም ፡ እምአሚሩ ፡ ዮሐንስ ፡ መጥመቅ ፡ ወበርተሎሜዎስ ፡ ወኢዮብ ፡ ጻድቅ ፡ ወራጉኤል ፡ መልአክ ፡
                                ....</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="187v" to="187v">187v</locus>a typical benediction for the scribe of the manuscript.</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="187v" to="188v">187v-188v</locus> a fragment of the Mastabeqwe' (መስተብቍዕ).</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="187v" to="188v">187v-188v</locus> penitential instructions in the lower margin in Amharic: የቈረበ ፡ ወርኅ ፡ ይከልከል ፡ ቃር ፡ ባቃረው ፡ ጊዜ ፡ አቡነ ፡ ዘበሰማያት ፡ የማያውቅ ፡
                                ተዝካር ፡ አይብላ ፡ ቢበላም : ቀን ፡ ይጹም ፡.</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="189r" to="190r">189r-190r</locus> an extract in Amharic of an 'Ordinance of the Church': በስመ ፡ … ሥርዓተ ፡ ቤተ ፡ ክርስቲዮን ፡ ቁርባን ፡ ምን ፡ ቀን ፡ ተዠመረ ፡ የጸሎት ፡ ሐሙስ
                                ፡ ዕ]ለት ፡ ማን ፡ ዠመረ ፡ ክርስቶስ ፡ አለ ፡ ማን ፡ ቈረቡ ፡ ሐዋርያት ፡ ከአልዓዛር ፡ ቤት ፡….</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="191r" to="191r">191r</locus> the end of a genealogy, different from the one recorded on 2r.</p>
                            <p>On <locus from="191v" to="191v">191v</locus> an Ethiopic syllabary in the halähamä order followed by ciphers.</p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="unknown" notBefore="1600" notAfter="1700">
                                <decoNote xml:id="b1">Ethiopic binding. Remnants of a quarter-leather covering that was adhered across the spine onto the boards. The outer sides of the boards are polished smooth
                                    from use, the exposed areas that were covered with leather are rougher and lighter in tone, and the inside faces or the board are similarly rough. Exposed spine and
                                    wooden boards; the back board has a split down the middle, this has been bound and rejoined with thick thread similar to the sewing, and appears to be contemporary
                                    with the binding. The back board also has two holes that appear to be from natural knots in the wood. Although the endbands are lost, sewing holes show they were
                                    anchored at every section. Unsupported sewing at 4 stations (two even pairs of sewing stations). The sewing is laced into the boards as an integral part of the
                                    sewing process and is done in separate pairs with each pair sewn using a different thread.</decoNote>
                                
                                <decoNote xml:id="b2">Raw hide leather satchel. The main container is made of a single piece of hide, folded up and sewn along the base and sides. Three flaps are attached to the top of
                                    the sides and back. The two at the sides fold over the top and are cut to meet. The back flap folds over them, slotting into a leather/hide strap (laced with
                                    leather thongs) that wraps horizontally around the top quarter of the satchel. A long leather strap is stitched to the inner top centre of the back panel and lies
                                    along the inside of the satchel emerging through a cut hole on the front panel towards the top edge, this is to assist in removing the manuscript from the satchel.
                                    All the hide of the satchel is faced inwards so that the hair side is in contact with the book. </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b3">Inside the satchel there is a lump of several pieces of leather laminated together, with the remnants of paper, adhesive and skinned paper on the reverse, on the top
                                    side the leather appears to have been blind tooled with a roll.  It appears to be a leather stop or part of a strap, whether it was part of this manuscript or not
                                    is not obvious.</decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b4"><dimensions type="satchel" unit="mm">
                                        <height>230</height>
                                        <width>210</width>
                                        <depth>102</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </decoNote>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
